10 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
11 This measure creates a new section in Article 10 of the Oklahoma
12 Constitution. This measure would allow for the value of the
13 taxpayer's tax liability, for the purposes of collecting ad
14 valorem taxes, to remain unchanged if inflation rate exceeds the
15 consumer price index's two percent (2%) targeted goal. The
16 value of a taxpayer's liability would remain frozen and
17 unchanged from the previous tax year. This freeze in the value
18 of liability would go into effect during the first assessment
19 year after the consumer price index information becomes
20 available.
